 0344                            logger?.LogWarn($"Unknown ARCOR2 \"{dispatch.@event}\" event received.");
 0345                            break;
 346                    }
 0347                }
 0348            }
 0349            catch(JsonException ex) {
 0350                logger?.LogError($"A JSON Exception occured while deserializing received ARCOR2 message.\n{ex}");
 0351            }
 0352            catch(Exception ex) {
 353                // Catch everything else, as we do not want the exception to bubble up to the WebSocket dispatcher
 354                // and close the connection. This is to increase compatibility between different ARCOR2 server
 355                // and client versions.
 0356                logger?.LogError($"An Exception occured while decoding a received ARCOR2 message.\n{ex}");
 0357            }
 0358        }

 0365                Signature = signature;

 742        /// <summary>
 743        ///     Establishes a connection to ARCOR2 server.
 744        /// </summary>
 745        /// <param name="domain">Domain of the ARCOR2 server</param>
 746        /// <param name="port">Port od the ARCOR2 server</param>
 747        /// <exception cref="UriFormatException" />
 748        /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException" />
 749        public async Task ConnectAsync(string domain, ushort port) =>
 0750            await ConnectAsync(new Uri($"ws://{domain}:{port}"));
 751
 752        /// <summary>
 753        ///     Establishes a connection to ARCOR2 server.
 754        /// </summary>
 755        /// <param name="uri">Full WebSocket URI</param>
 756        /// <exception cref="UriFormatException" />
 757        /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException" />
 758        /// <exception cref="Arcor2ConnectionException"> When inner WebSocket fails to connect.</exception>
 0759        public async Task ConnectAsync(Uri uri) {
 760            // Other parameters are implicitly validated by the parameter being Uri type.
 0761            if(uri.Scheme != "ws" && uri.Scheme != "wss") {
 0762                throw new UriFormatException("The URI scheme must be 'ws' or 'wss'.");
 763            }
 764
 0765            if(webSocket.State != WebSocketState.None) {
 0766                throw new InvalidOperationException("ConnectAsync can not be invoked when connection is not opened.");
 767            }
 768
 0769            try {
 0770                await webSocket.ConnectAsync(uri);
 0771            }
 0772            catch(WebSocketConnectionException e) {
 0773                throw new Arcor2ConnectionException("WebSocket failed to connect.", e);
 774            }
 775
 0776            Uri = uri;
 0777        }
 778
 779        /// <summary>
 780        ///     Closes a connection to ARCOR2 sever.
 781        /// </summary>
 782        /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException"></exception>
 0783        public async Task CloseAsync() {
 0784            if(webSocket.State != WebSocketState.Open) {
 0785                throw new InvalidOperationException("CloseAsync can not be invoked when connection is not open.");
 786            }
 787
 0788            await webSocket.CloseAsync();
 0789            Uri = null;
 0790        }

 795
 796        /// <summary>
 797        ///     Sends a request and waits for a response with the matching ID.
 798        /// </summary>
 799        /// <param name="message">Request object to be serialized and sent</param>
 800        /// <param name="id">ID of the request. Will increment and assign from <see cref="requestId" /> if null. </param
 801        /// <param name="rpcSignature">Name of the RPC used by the server.</param>
 802        /// <returns>Response message</returns>
 803        /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException">Thrown when connection is not open</exception>
 804        /// <exception cref="TimeoutException">Thrown when response is not received within timeout period</exception>
 0805        private async Task<string> SendAndWaitAsync(string message, int id, string rpcSignature) {
 0806            if(webSocket.State != WebSocketState.Open) {
 0807                throw new InvalidOperationException("Cannot send message when connection is not open.");
 808            }
 809
 0810            var pendingRequest = new PendingRequest(clientSettings.RpcTimeout, rpcSignature);
 811
 0812            if(!pendingRequests.TryAdd(id, pendingRequest)) {
 0813                throw new InvalidOperationException($"Request ID {id} already exists.");
 814            }
 815
 0816            try {
 0817                await webSocket.SendAsync(message);
 0818                logger?.LogInfo($"Sent a new ARCOR2 message:\n{message}");
 0819                return await pendingRequest.TaskCompletionSource.Task;
 820            }
 0821            finally {
 0822                pendingRequests.TryRemove(id, out _);
 0823                pendingRequest.CancellationTokenSource.Dispose();
 0824            }
 0825        }
 826
 827        /// <summary>
 828        ///     Sends a request and waits for a response with the matching ID
 829        /// </summary>
 830        /// <typeparam name="T">The object type to be serialized</typeparam>
 831        /// <param name="message">Request object to be serialized and sent</param>
 832        /// <param name="id">ID of the request.</param>
 833        /// <param name="rpcSignature">Name of the RPC used by the server.</param>
 834        /// <returns>Response message</returns>
 835        /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException">Thrown when connection is not open</exception>
 836        /// <exception cref="TimeoutException">Thrown when response is not received within timeout period</exception>
 837        private async Task<string> SendAndWaitAsync<T>(T message, int id, string rpcSignature) =>
 0838            await SendAndWaitAsync(JsonConvert.SerializeObject(message), id, rpcSignature);
 839

 01219            switch(packageChanged.ChangeType) {

 01221                    PackageAdded?.Invoke(this, new PackageEventArgs(packageChanged.Data));
 01222                    break;
 1223                case PackageChanged.ChangeTypeEnum.Update:
 01224                    PackageUpdated?.Invoke(this, new PackageEventArgs(packageChanged.Data));
 01225                    break;
 1226                case PackageChanged.ChangeTypeEnum.Remove:
 01227                    PackageRemoved?.Invoke(this, new PackageEventArgs(packageChanged.Data));
 01228                    break;
 1229                case PackageChanged.ChangeTypeEnum.UpdateBase:
 01230                    throw new NotImplementedException("PackageChanged base update should never occur.");
 1231                default:
 01232                    throw new NotImplementedException("Unknown change type for 'PackageChanged' event.");
 1233            }
